The paper discusses the concept of human-aware planning, which involves generating plans that are explicable to a human observer and providing explanations when such plans cannot be generated. This is a topic that falls under the intersection of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), machine learning (cs.LG), and systems and control (cs.SY). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
